                </h3>
                <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-6">
                    Handles GET requests to retrieve all instances of the model with support for
                    pagination, filtering, and both synchronous/asynchronous operations.
                </p>
                
                <div class="function-signature">
                    <h4 class="font-bold text-lg mb-2">get_all(req, res, query_params)</h4>
                    <p class="text-light-text-secondary mb-3">Route: <code>GET /api/{model_name}</code></p>
                    
                    <table class="param-table">
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Parameter</th>
                                <th>Type</th>
                                <th>Description</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>req</td>
                                <td>table</td>
                                <td>The request object</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>res</td>
                                <td>table</td>
                                <td>The response object</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>query_params</td>
                                <td>table</td>
                                <td>Query parameters from the URL</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                    
                    <p class="mt-3"><strong>Supported Query Parameters:</strong></p>
                    <ul class="list-disc ml-6 mt-2">
                        <li><code>page</code> - Page number for pagination (default: 1)</li>
                        <li><code>limit</code> - Number of records per page (default: depends on model)</li>
                        <li><code>order_by</code> - Column to order by</li>
                        <li><code>order_direction</code> - Order direction (ASC/DESC)</li>
                        <li>Any model field name - For filtering (e.g., <code>?name=John</code>)</li>
                    </ul>
                    
                    <p class="mt-3"><strong>Returns:</strong> JSON array of records or pagination object</p>
                    <p class="mt-2"><strong>HTTP Status Codes:</strong> 200 (Success), 500 (Internal Server Error)</p>
                </div>
                
                <div class="bg-gray-800 text-gray-200 rounded-lg p-6 code-block mb-6">
                    <div class="flex justify-between items-center mb-4">
                        <h4 class="text-lg font-bold">GET All Examples</h4>
                        <button class="bg-laser-blue text-white px-3 py-1 rounded text-sm hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors copy-btn">
                            <i class="fas fa-copy mr-1"></i>Copy
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <pre class="overflow-x-auto text-sm"><code><span class="code-comment">-- Get all users</span>
<span class="code-comment">-- Request: GET /api/users</span>
<span class="code-comment">-- Response: [{"id":1,"name":"John"},{"id":2,"name":"Jane"}]</span>

<span class="code-comment">-- Get users with pagination</span>
<span class="code-comment">-- Request: GET /api/users?page=1&limit=10</span>
<span class="code-comment">-- Response: {"data":[{"id":1,"name":"John"},...],"pagination":{"page":1,"per_page":10,"total":100}}</span>

<span class="code-comment">-- Get users with filtering</span>
